# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION A — SHARED / MONOREPO-WIDE RULES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## A1. Shared Packages (`packages/`)

- **`@kavach/shared-types`** is the single source of truth for all enums and interfaces.
  Always import from this package rather than redefining types locally in any app.
  Current core types (DO NOT re-declare in app code):
  `Role`, `Device`, `DeviceStatus`, `DeviceType`, `AppCategory`, `Rule`, `RuleType`,
  `Alert`, `AlertType`, `AlertSeverity`, `FocusSession`, `Subscription`, `PlanType`,
  `User`, `StudentProfile`, `Tenant`, `AIInsight`, `Badge`, `BadgeType`

- **`@kavach/shared-constants`** holds app-wide constants:
  `APP_CATEGORIES`, `BLOCKED_CATEGORIES_DEFAULT`, `PLAN_LIMITS`, `FOCUS_PRESETS`,
  `WEEK_DAYS`, `DEVICE_LINK_CODE_LENGTH`. Use them — do not duplicate.

- **`@kavach/shared-utils`** holds utility functions. Add new utilities here if
  they are needed by ≥ 2 apps.

- All packages export raw TypeScript — they are transpiled by Next.js
  (`transpilePackages` in [apps/web-app/next.config.js](mdc:apps/web-app/next.config.js))
  and consumed directly by Electron (tsc) and Expo (Metro bundler).
  Do NOT add a build step or compile to JS inside `packages/`.

## A2. TypeScript (All Apps)

- `strict: true` is ON in every `tsconfig.json`. No implicit `any`.
- No `any` unless justified with an inline comment explaining why it cannot be avoided.
- All public function signatures must be fully typed (params + return type).
- Prefer types from `@kavach/shared-types` over local re-declarations.
- Use `unknown` instead of `any` when the shape is genuinely unknown, then narrow.

Naming conventions (non-negotiable across all apps):

| Construct          | Convention           | Example                     |
|--------------------|----------------------|-----------------------------|
| Components / Classes | PascalCase         | `DeviceCard`, `RuleSync`    |
| Variables / params | camelCase            | `deviceList`, `focusScore`  |
| Constants          | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE     | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`           |
| Hooks              | `use` + camelCase    | `useDevices`, `useFocusMode`|
| Files (TS/TSX)     | PascalCase for classes/components, camelCase for modules | `EnforcementEngine.ts`, `axios.ts` |
| Enums              | PascalCase           | `Role.STUDENT`              |

## A3. Environment Variables

- **No hardcoded URLs, API keys, tokens, or credentials** anywhere in source code — ever.
- All env config goes in `.env` files. `.env` files MUST be in `.gitignore`.
  Each app has an `env.example` — keep it updated when you add a new variable.
- When adding a new `process.env.*` reference in web-app, also add a fallback
  in [apps/web-app/next.config.js](mdc:apps/web-app/next.config.js) `env: {}` block so Vercel builds don't crash.
- Known env variables per app:

  **web-app**: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SHOW_DEMO_CREDENTIALS`, `NEXT_OUTPUT`, `SKIP_PWA`
  **desktop-agent**: `KAVACH_API_URL` (from [apps/desktop-agent/env.example](mdc:apps/desktop-agent/env.example))
  **mobile**: see [apps/mobile/env.example](mdc:apps/mobile/env.example)
  **backend**: `SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `CORS_ORIGINS`, etc.

## A4. Security & Production Safety

- No `console.log` in production code anywhere in the monorepo.
  Desktop agent uses a file logger; web-app and mobile should use a logger utility.
- Sanitize all user inputs before processing or sending to APIs.
- Tokens are stored in `localStorage` (web) and `AsyncStorage` (mobile) — never log them.
- Backend: all requests MUST go through JWT filter (`JwtFilter.java`).
  Tenant isolation is enforced by extracting `tenantId` from the JWT claim in every service.

## A5. Git, Branching & PR Rules

Branch naming:
```
feat/<feature-name>       → New features
fix/<issue-name>          → Bug fixes
refactor/<module-name>    → Refactors
hotfix/<issue-name>       → Production hotfixes
```

PR rules:
- ALL PRs target the `dev` branch. **Never directly to `main`.**
- Maximum 2 commits per PR. Squash if needed.
- Maximum 5 bug fixes OR 1 feature/refactor per PR.
- No self-merging — all PRs reviewed by @Prateek Saxena.
- Only TL can merge into `main`.
- CI pipeline (`ci.yml`) MUST be green before merge.
  It runs: type-check, lint, jest (web-app + mobile + desktop-agent), Maven tests (backend).

Every PR MUST include:
```
✅ Clear description of what changed and why
✅ Screenshots (if any UI changes)
✅ API contract changes documented (if backend changes)
✅ Test coverage update confirmed
✅ No new `any` types without justification
✅ Shared package changes impact noted
```

🚫 DO NOT TOUCH: `main` branch directly. Husky is configured (`husky || true`).

