## D1. Folder Structure

```
apps/mobile/src/
├── screens/                   ← Screen components (one per route)
│   ├── LoginScreen.tsx
│   ├── DashboardScreen.tsx
│   ├── FocusScreen.tsx
│   ├── AchievementsScreen.tsx
│   ├── RewardsScreen.tsx
│   └── StudyBuddyScreen.tsx
├── components/                ← Reusable UI components
├── context/AuthContext.tsx    ← Auth state (JWT + deviceId)
├── navigation/AppNavigator.tsx← React Navigation stack/tab navigator
├── lib/                       ← API call functions (one file per domain)
│   ├── axios.ts               ← Axios instance with JWT interceptor
│   ├── auth.ts                ← Login/logout/me API calls
│   ├── studentApi.ts          ← Student dashboard data
│   ├── focusApi.ts            ← Focus session API
│   ├── badgesApi.ts           ← Badges/achievements API
│   └── ...                    ← One file per API domain
├── enforcement/
│   ├── RuleSync.ts            ← Rule fetching/caching via AsyncStorage
│   └── OverlayManager.ts      ← Overlay display logic
├── tasks/
│   ├── AppWatcherTask.ts      ← Background enforcement (expo-task-manager, 15s cycle)
│   ├── UsageCollectorTask.ts  ← Background usage reporting
│   ├── GeoFenceTask.ts        ← Location-based enforcement
│   └── LocationTask.ts        ← Location tracking
├── permissions/               ← Permission request flows (PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS, etc.)
└── __tests__/                 ← Jest tests
    ├── context/
    ├── lib/
    └── screens/
```

## D2. Critical Architecture Rules

- **`AppWatcherTask`** (15-second cycle) is the enforcement backbone on Android.
  It queries `UsageStatsManager` (native module) for the foreground app and
  cross-checks against `RuleSync` cached rules. Do not change the task name
  `KAVACH_APP_WATCHER` — it is registered at app launch.

- **Background tasks** use `expo-task-manager` + `expo-background-fetch`.
  Register tasks in `App.tsx` on login. Never register inside a component render.

- **Rule caching** is done via `AsyncStorage`. Rules are cached under a fixed key by `RuleSync`.
  Always read rules from the cache in background tasks — never make a live API call
  inside the 15-second loop unless the version is stale.

- **Auth tokens** are stored in `AsyncStorage` (not SecureStore — see existing `auth.ts`).
  Token keys must match what `lib/axios.ts` reads. Do not introduce new key names.

- **Overlays** (red/blue/amber) are implemented via native modules and `OverlayManager.ts`.
  Do not attempt to replicate overlay logic with React Native Modals — they cannot
  render over other apps.

- Android requires `PACKAGE_USAGE_STATS` and `SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW` permissions.
  Handle permission denial gracefully — never crash if they are not granted.

## D3. UI Standards (Mobile)

- Use **React Navigation** for all navigation. No Expo Router in this app.
- Use **Victory Native** for charts (`victory-native`).
- Use `@expo/vector-icons` for icons.
- No inline styles — use StyleSheet.create() for all styles.
- Components must NOT exceed 200 lines. Refactor screens into sub-components.

## D4. Testing (Mobile)

- Framework: **Jest + jest-expo + @testing-library/react-native**.
- Tests live in `src/__tests__/`.
- Run: `pnpm test` or `pnpm test:coverage`.
- Native modules (`UsageStatsManager`, `OverlayModule`) must be mocked.
- Background task logic must be testable without the native task runner.
- CI runs `pnpm test:coverage` — ensure tests pass in the `ubuntu-latest` CI environment.

## D5. Build & Distribution

- Local dev: `pnpm start` or `pnpm android`.
- EAS builds: `pnpm build:android` (preview) or `pnpm build:android:prod` (production).
- Never commit `android/` or `ios/` native directories — use `expo prebuild` to generate them.

