# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION E — BACKEND (Spring Boot 3 / Java 17)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Reference: [backend/](mdc:backend)

## E1. Folder Structure

```
backend/src/main/java/com/kavach/
├── auth/                      ← JWT filter, auth controller, token service
├── config/                    ← App config beans (RequestIdFilter, etc.)
├── security/SecurityConfig.java ← Spring Security chain (CORS, JWT, roles)
└── <domain>/                  ← One package per domain (device, blocking, focus, etc.)
    ├── <Domain>Controller.java ← REST controller (@RestController)
    ├── <Domain>Service.java    ← Business logic
    ├── <Domain>Repository.java ← Spring Data JPA repository
    └── <Domain>Dto.java        ← Request/Response DTOs (never expose JPA entity directly)
```

## E2. API Rules

- All endpoints are prefixed with `/api/v1/`.
- All protected endpoints require a valid JWT — enforced by `JwtFilter.java`.
- `SUPER_ADMIN`, `INSTITUTE_ADMIN`, `IT_HEAD`, `PRINCIPAL`, `PARENT`, `STUDENT`
  are the valid roles. Enforce role checks with `@PreAuthorize` or service-level checks.
- **Never expose JPA entities directly in API responses** — always use DTOs.
- Tenant isolation: every service method MUST scope DB queries to the `tenantId`
  extracted from the JWT. Never trust a tenant ID passed in the request body.
- Increment `rulesVersion` in `EnforcementState` whenever blocking rules change —
  this triggers desktop agent and mobile re-sync.

## E3. CORS

- Allowed origins are controlled by the `CORS_ORIGINS` environment variable
  (read in [backend/src/main/java/com/kavach/security/SecurityConfig.java](mdc:backend/src/main/java/com/kavach/security/SecurityConfig.java)).
- All `OPTIONS` preflight requests are explicitly permitted via
  `.requestMatchers(HttpMethod.OPTIONS, "/**").permitAll()` — do not remove this.
- When deploying to a new frontend URL, add it to `CORS_ORIGINS` in the Railway dashboard.

## E4. Database & Migrations

- ORM: Spring Data JPA / Hibernate.
- Schema is managed via SQL migration scripts in `src/main/resources/` (not Flyway/Liquibase).
- Never drop or alter a column in a migration without a corresponding data migration.

## E5. Testing (Backend)

- Framework: **JUnit 5 + Spring Boot Test + Mockito**.
- Tests live in `backend/src/test/`.
- CI runs `mvn verify jacoco:report -B` which executes all tests and generates coverage.
- SonarCloud scans run on CI — maintain code quality gates.
- Every new service method MUST have a corresponding unit test.

## E6. Configuration

- Application config is in [backend/src/main/resources/application.yml](mdc:backend/src/main/resources/application.yml).
- No duplicate YAML keys — YAML is strict about duplicate keys at the same level
  (this caused a Railway crash — see the `springdoc.swagger-ui.enabled` incident).
- Secrets (JWT secret, DB password) MUST come from environment variables, not hardcoded.

